42- year- old Augustine Ilodibe Jnr, son of the late billionaire transporter and owner of Ekene Dili Chukwu Motors has been reported dead. According to a press release from his family in Lagos, the young Ilodibe Jnr died from COVID-19 complications. The release reads: “With great sadness, we announce the passing unto glory our dear son, husband, father, brother and uncle, Ekendilichukwu Augustine Chukwunonso ILODIBE (Junior) who died this morning from complications of COVID-19 in Lagos. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! We pray that his soul rests in peace and the Lord comfort his family and all of us he left behind. In consideration of the current pandemic, we kindly ask that you respect and maintain safety protocols through calls and messages to the family rather than physical visits. JUST IN: Saudi Arabia ‘To Open Airspace, Land, Sea Border’ With Qatar COVID-19: Kano Residents Plead For Enforcement Of Protocols In Public Places Thank you and God bless. Mr Obinna ILODIBE (on behalf of the family)CKN NIGERIA Published: January 04, 2021MAY HIS SOUL REST IN PEACE SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION